name: Eddy Achterberg
comments: Former Dutch soccer player and coach, who went to play for FC Twente in 1967 playing 246 games in the Eredivisie scoring 26 goals. The midfielder played in 27 UEFA Cup matches for Twente reaching the semi-finals in the 1972–1973 season and the finals during the 1973–1974 season, where the club lost to Borussia Mönchengladbach. Achterberg, along with other players and fans of FC Twente, released a song entitled "Eenmaal zullen wij de kampioenen zijn" (Once we will be the Champions) in the successful 1973/4 season, which became the unofficial club anthem.
